Arrival and Departure Final Models: EXCLUDING AI, GOA, WCTRI

This is a cleaned version of 04_24_19 Temp link trait fish.Rmd/11_20_19_Temp_link_traits_fish.Rmd. Changes * improved formatting * easier to follow * species and region as random effects * scaling temperature values * setting nACQ to 0, see why here.

library(MuMIn)
library(lme4)
library(data.table)
library(ggplot2)
library(here)
library(wesanderson) # to color plots

spp_master_ztemp_seus_buoy_scaled <- readRDS(here("Data","Spp_master", "spp_master_ztemp_seus_buoy_scaled.rds"))

Delete all observations of regions that do not sample every year

levels(spp_master_ztemp_seus_buoy_scaled$reg)
[1] "ai"    "ebs"   "gmex"  "goa"   "neus"  "newf"  "sa"    "shelf" "wctri"
spp_master_ztemp_seus_buoy_scaled_annual_obs <- spp_master_ztemp_seus_buoy_scaled[!(reg %in% c("ai","goa","wctri")),]

Running, and ranking arrival models without traits

##Here, I scaled all temperature values across all regions, and included species as a random effect. In order to do this, I had to change the algorithm slightly–nAGQ = 0.

#names of scaled columns
variables_scaled <- grep("*_scaled", names(spp_master_ztemp_seus_buoy_scaled_annual_obs), value = T)

#going to make loop to make all models I need to look at with a single temperature variable

arrival_model_comparison_annual_obs <- as.data.table(matrix(nrow = length(variables_scaled)))
arrival_model_comparison_annual_obs[, variable:=as.factor(V1)][, coef:=as.numeric(V1)][, p_value:=as.numeric(V1)][, AICc:=as.numeric(V1)]
arrival_model_comparison_annual_obs[, V1 := NULL]

for (i in 1:length(variables_scaled)){
  mod <- glmer(col ~ get(variables_scaled[i]) + (1|reg) + (1|spp), family = binomial, data = spp_master_ztemp_seus_buoy_scaled_annual_obs, nAGQ = 0)
  arrival_model_comparison_annual_obs[i,variable := variables_scaled[i]]
  arrival_model_comparison_annual_obs[i,coef := coef(summary(mod))[,"Estimate"][2]]
  arrival_model_comparison_annual_obs[i,p_value := coef(summary(mod))[,"Pr(>|z|)"][2]]
  arrival_model_comparison_annual_obs[i,AICc := AICc(mod)]
  
  print(paste(i, length(variables_scaled), sep = "/"))
    
}

Relative Variable Importance

NB: I didn’t end up using mean as a predictor variable (patterns captured in min and max, less relevant to thermal niche)

arrival_model_comparison_annual_obs_nomean <- arrival_model_comparison_annual_obs[!grepl("mean",variable),]

departure_model_comparison_annual_obs_nomean <- departure_model_comparison_annual_obs[!grepl("mean",variable),]

How does the null model with only random effects perform?

#add null to tables
intercept_arrival_mod_scaled <- glmer(col ~ (1|spp) + (1|reg), family = binomial, nAGQ = 0, data = spp_master_ztemp_seus_buoy_scaled_annual_obs)

intercept_departure_mod_scaled <- glmer(now_ext ~ (1|reg) + (1|spp), family = binomial, data = spp_master_ztemp_seus_buoy_scaled_annual_obs, nAGQ = 0)

#best model better than null? yes
AICc(intercept_arrival_mod_scaled)-min(arrival_model_comparison_annual_obs$AICc)

Relative Variable Importance for Arrival Models

#add ∆AIC to tables
min_arrival_AICc <- min(arrival_model_comparison_annual_obs_nomean[, AICc])
arrival_model_comparison_annual_obs_nomean[,"deltaAICc" := (AICc - min_arrival_AICc)]

#add relative likelihood exp( -0.5 * ∆AIC score for that model)
arrival_model_comparison_annual_obs_nomean[,"rel_likelihood" := exp((-0.5 * deltaAICc))]
#sum relative likelihoods across all models
arrival_model_comparison_annual_obs_nomean.likelihoodsum <- sum(arrival_model_comparison_annual_obs_nomean[, rel_likelihood])
#Akaike weight for a model is this rel_likelihood divided by the sum of these values across all models
arrival_model_comparison_annual_obs_nomean[,"akaike_weight" := rel_likelihood/arrival_model_comparison_annual_obs_nomean.likelihoodsum]

#I want to look at relative importance FOR:

#bottom/surface (bottom = includes sbt, grepl("sbt", variable))
arrival_bottom_importance <- sum(arrival_model_comparison_annual_obs_nomean[grep("sbt", variable), ]$akaike_weight)
arrival_surface_importance <- sum(arrival_model_comparison_annual_obs_nomean[grep("sst", variable), ]$akaike_weight)

#lag/not lagged (grepl("lag", variable))
arrival_lag_importance <- sum(arrival_model_comparison_annual_obs_nomean[grep("lag", variable), ]$akaike_weight)
arrival_nolag_importance <- sum(arrival_model_comparison_annual_obs_nomean[!grep("lag", variable), ]$akaike_weight)

#absolute (grepl("abs", variable))
arrival_abs_importance <- sum(arrival_model_comparison_annual_obs_nomean[grep("abs", variable), ]$akaike_weight)

#raw (!grepl("change"))
arrival_raw_importance <- sum(arrival_model_comparison_annual_obs_nomean[!grep("change", variable), ]$akaike_weight)

#change (grepl("change", variable), (!grepl("abs")))
arrival_change_importance <- sum(arrival_model_comparison_annual_obs_nomean[grep("change", variable), ][!grep("abs", variable),]$akaike_weight)

#type of temp variable (max, min, seas)
arrival_max_temp_importance <- sum(arrival_model_comparison_annual_obs_nomean[grep("max", variable), ]$akaike_weight)
arrival_min_temp_importance <- sum(arrival_model_comparison_annual_obs_nomean[grep("min", variable), ]$akaike_weight)
arrival_seas_temp_importance <- sum(arrival_model_comparison_annual_obs_nomean[grep("seas", variable), ]$akaike_weight)

arrival_model_comparison_annual_obs_nomean_akaikeweights <- arrival_model_comparison_annual_obs_nomean

saveRDS(arrival_model_comparison_annual_obs_nomean_akaikeweights, file = here("Model_results","arrival_model_comparison_annual_obs_nomean_akaikeweights_annual_obs.rds"))
saveRDS(arrival_model_comparison_annual_obs_nomean_akaikeweights, file = here("tables","arrival_model_comparison_annual_obs_nomean_akaikeweights_annual_obs.rds"))
arrival_model_comparison_annual_obs_nomean_akaikeweights <- readRDS(file = here("Model_results","arrival_model_comparison_annual_obs_nomean_akaikeweights_annual_obs.rds"))

Relative Variable Importance Departure Models

#add ∆AIC to tables
min_departure_AICc <- min(departure_model_comparison_annual_obs_nomean[, AICc])
departure_model_comparison_annual_obs_nomean[,"deltaAICc" := (AICc - min_departure_AICc)]

#add relative likelihood exp( -0.5 * ∆AIC score for that model)
departure_model_comparison_annual_obs_nomean[,"rel_likelihood" := exp((-0.5 * deltaAICc))]
#sum relative likelihoods across all models
departure_model_comparison_annual_obs_nomean.likelihoodsum <- sum(departure_model_comparison_annual_obs_nomean[, rel_likelihood])
#Akaike weight for a model is this rel_likelihood devided by the sum of these values across all models
departure_model_comparison_annual_obs_nomean[,"akaike_weight" := rel_likelihood/departure_model_comparison_annual_obs_nomean.likelihoodsum]
